1 A BILL for an Act to create and enact a new section to chapter 54-35 of the North Dakota
2 Century Code, relating to the creation of a legislative committee on government efficiency.
3 BE IT ENACTED BY THE LEGISLATIVE ASSEMBLY OF NORTH DAKOTA:
4 SECTION 1. A new section to chapter 54-35 of the North Dakota Century Code is created
5 and enacted as follows:
6 Legislative committee on government efficiency - Members - Duties - Report to the
7 legislative management.
8 1. The legislative management, during each biennium, shall appoint a legislative
9 committee on government efficiency.
10 2. The membership of the committee must consist of at least one member from each
11 standing committee of the house of representatives and the senate, who served during
12 the most recently completed regular session of the legislative assembly. The
13 legislative management shall designate the chairman and appoint all members of the
14 committee consistent with this subsection.
15 3. The committee shall meet monthly and operate according to the statutes and
16 procedure governing the operation of other legislative management interim
17 committees.
18 4. The committee shall:
19 a. Review and analyze budgets and reports from executive branch agencies,
20 boards, and commissions and the supreme court.
21 b. Collaborate with and receive testimony from executive branch agencies, boards,
22 and commissions and the supreme court to identify areas to increase efficiency,
23 methods to implement cos t - saving measures, determine areas of state
24 government deemed unnecessary or duplicative, target outdated or overly
